            ? - Yes I was married to him on the 4th of May la in <placeName id="t17790915-66-crimeloc337">Catherine-Cree Church, Leadenhall-street</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t17790915-66-crimeloc337" type="placeName" value="Catherine-Cree Church, Leadenhall-street"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t17790915-66-crimeloc337" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t17790915-66-off335 t17790915-66-crimeloc337"></join>. Some time after I married him he went down to Yorkshire; in the mean time I received a letter from his wife, directed to him, dated Netherthong, June the 30th, that was the first time I suspected his being a married man; I carried the letter to Mr. Alderman Plomer.</p>
               <p>Do you know what her maiden name was? - 
               
                  <persName id="t17790915-66-victim663" type="victimName">
                     Mary
                      Portsmouth
                  <interp inst="t17790915-66-victim663" type="surname" value="Portsmouth"></interp>
